result.execSummary:
All charges against James Jesse Cubit in this case have been dismissed. These charges were not proven and have no legal effect. James Jesse Cubit is presumed innocent.

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

records.addlTxt: Defendant James Jesse Cubit not in court.  Attorney Anthony Joseph Pozorski Sr. in court for State of Wisconsin. DA attempt to contact Mississippi has not been successful to confirm extradition. State moves to dismiss. Case dismissed.

Defendant James Jesse Cubit not in court.  Attorney Lisa Riniker in court for State of Wisconsin. State heard. Status of Mississippi case unkown. DA Riniker steps outside to call Mississippi District Attorney for more information. DA Riniker returns--no information. Court continues extradition hearing for further information. Extradition hearing set. Defendant appears at 1:25. Defendant heard and states probation is complete. Payment arrangements have been made with his agent. Court will confirm warrant was withdrawn at next hearing. Defendant does not need to appear.
Extradition hearing scheduled for June 13, 2022 at 11:30 am.

Defendant James Jesse Cubit appears in court, in custody at Grant County Jail. Attorney Anthony Pozorksi appears in court for the State of Wisconsin. State swears to the extradition complaint. Court explains complaint, right to counsel, and extradition rights. Defendant referred to SPD. State requests $250 cash bond. Court orders $100 cash bond. Extradition hearing set.
Extradition hearing on May 23, 2022 at 01:00 pm.
